Can you use this to golf the `Mul` instance on tensor products?

> Can you use this to golf the `Mul` instance on tensor products?

done
Once you've added the docstring, please run a benchmark (it will fail at the moment because the missing docstring will cause a linter error)
!bench

Here are the [benchmark results](http://speed.lean-fro.org/mathlib4/run-detail/28c70f20-ceb5-4dc7-a310-7e97d3877225) for commit ef495da35b42099329f106fcc1834751812a50c8.
There were [significant changes](http://speed.lean-fro.org/mathlib4/compare/97644644-6f0a-4182-ad51-f1b5671859c2/to/28c70f20-ceb5-4dc7-a310-7e97d3877225) against commit c8bd1526ad5d918c301b21352da030a97cab03f3:
```diff
  Benchmark                     Metric         Change
  ===================================================
- ~Mathlib.RingTheory.Kaehler   instructions     5.8%
```
How do we feel about the benchmark result. Is the slow down statistically insignificant?
bors merge
I think it's ok; I tried golfing this a long time ago in #6195 and got a timeout; 5% is a much less bad outcome!

Thanks for the reminder, didn't notice the missing doc string
I think an explanation in terms of binary functions might be useful too, to explain the relation with `map`; that `map f g (m1  n1) (m2  n2) = f m1 m2  g m1 m2`.
Thanks! I kept both version

